```

### 5.3 Integration Testing

Integration testing verifies the notification system works correctly with other system components:

```javascript
// Integration test example
async function integrationTest() {
  // Simulate user action that should trigger notification
  const user = await createTestUser();
  const order = await createTestOrder(user);
  await processOrder(order);

  // Verify notification was sent correctly
  const notifications = await getNotificationsForUser(user);
  return notifications.some(n => 
    n.recipient === "contact@contact.com" && 
    n.content.includes("confirmation")
  );
}
```

---

## 6. TOOL-BASED TESTING APPROACH

For comprehensive notification testing, a standardized tool-based approach ensures consistency and repeatability. This section details the recommended tools and methods for notification testing.

### 6.1 Notification Testing Tools

The notification system provides specialized testing tools to simplify validation:

| Tool | Purpose | Key Features |
|------|---------|-------------|
| notification-cli | Command-line testing utility | Quick tests, CI/CD integration, Batch testing |
| NotificationTestClient | Programmable test client | Full API access, Mock capabilities, Detailed reporting |
| TestEmailServer | Email verification server | Captures all test emails, Content validation, Attachment verification |
| NotificationValidator | Automated test validator | Verification rules, Compliance checking, Test case management |

### 6.2 Tool Interface Patterns

The notification testing tools follow consistent interface patterns for ease of use:

#### 6.2.1 Standard Tool Call Format

Tool operations typically follow this standard format:

```json
{
  "tool_call": {
    "name": "[tool_name]",
    "arguments": {
      "[argument_name]": "[argument_value]",
      ...
    }
  }
}
```

#### 6.2.2 Common Testing Tools

The following tools are most commonly used for notification testing:

| Tool Name | Purpose | Required Arguments | Optional Arguments |
|-----------|---------|-------------------|-------------------|
| send_email | Send test email | To, Body | Subject, Format, Attachments |
| verify_delivery | Check delivery status | MessageId | Timeout, CheckRecipient |
| validate_content | Validate message content | MessageId, ExpectedContent | IgnoreCase, PartialMatch |
| simulate_error | Test error handling | ErrorType | ErrorParameters |

